This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for pedestrian localization, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of neural networks and data augmentation also suggests that it could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the robustness of the algorithm against attacks, indicating that it could also fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
